### FreshBox O2C – HTTP Test Suite
### Use with VSCode REST Client extension or import into Thunder Client
### Base URL: http://localhost:4004

@base = http://localhost:4004/api/o2c

### ─── MASTER DATA ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Get all Customers
GET {{base}}/Customers

### Get all Products
GET {{base}}/Products

### ─── STEP 1: CREATE INQUIRY ───────────────────────────────────────────

### Create Inquiry INQ000001
POST {{base}}/Inquiries
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ID": "INQ000001",
  "customer_ID": "TECH01",
  "inquiryDate": "2025-01-15",
  "validUntil": "2025-01-22",
  "notes": "Need 120 meal boxes for 2 days – Lunch and Dinner",
  "status": "Open",
  "items": [
    { "product_ID": "MEAL-VEG", "requestedQty": 80 },
    { "product_ID": "MEAL-NVG", "requestedQty": 40 }
  ]
}

### List all Inquiries
GET {{base}}/Inquiries?$expand=customer,items($expand=product)

### ─── STEP 2: CONVERT TO QUOTATION ────────────────────────────────────

### Convert Inquiry to Quotation with 15% discount
POST {{base}}/Inquiries('INQ000001')/O2CService.convertToQuotation
Content-Type: application/json

{ "discountPct": 15 }

### List all Quotations
GET {{base}}/Quotations?$expand=customer,items($expand=product)

### ─── STEP 3: ACCEPT QUOTATION → SALES ORDER ──────────────────────────

### Accept Quotation (use ID from step 2 response, e.g. QT000001)
POST {{base}}/Quotations('QT000001')/O2CService.acceptQuotation
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### List Sales Orders
GET {{base}}/SalesOrders?$expand=customer,items($expand=product)

### Get SO Items (to find UUIDs for delivery)
GET {{base}}/SalesOrderItems?$filter=salesOrder_ID eq 'SO000001'&$expand=product

### ─── STEP 4A: DELIVERY 1 – LUNCH BATCH ───────────────────────────────

### Create Delivery 1 (replace UUIDs with actual from SO items response)
POST {{base}}/SalesOrders('SO000001')/O2CService.createDelivery
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "batchLabel": "Lunch Batch – Day 1",
  "plannedDate": "2025-01-16",
  "items": [
    { "soItemId": "REPLACE-WITH-VEG-ITEM-UUID", "qty": 40 },
    { "soItemId": "REPLACE-WITH-NVG-ITEM-UUID", "qty": 20 }
  ]
}

### Post Goods Issue – Delivery 1
POST {{base}}/Deliveries('DL000001')/O2CService.postGoodsIssue
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### ─── STEP 4B: DELIVERY 2 – DINNER BATCH ──────────────────────────────

### Create Delivery 2
POST {{base}}/SalesOrders('SO000001')/O2CService.createDelivery
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "batchLabel": "Dinner Batch – Day 2",
  "plannedDate": "2025-01-17",
  "items": [
    { "soItemId": "REPLACE-WITH-VEG-ITEM-UUID", "qty": 40 },
    { "soItemId": "REPLACE-WITH-NVG-ITEM-UUID", "qty": 20 }
  ]
}

### Post Goods Issue – Delivery 2
POST {{base}}/Deliveries('DL000002')/O2CService.postGoodsIssue
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### List Deliveries
GET {{base}}/Deliveries?$expand=customer,items($expand=product)

### ─── STEP 5: CREATE INVOICE ───────────────────────────────────────────

### Create Invoice from both deliveries
POST {{base}}/createInvoiceFromDeliveries
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "deliveryIds": ["DL000001", "DL000002"],
  "invoiceDate": "2025-01-17",
  "dueDate": "2025-02-16"
}

### View Invoice with full GST breakup
GET {{base}}/Invoices?$expand=customer,items($expand=product),deliveries($expand=delivery)

### ─── STEP 6: MARK PAID ────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Mark Invoice as Paid
POST {{base}}/Invoices('IV000001')/O2CService.markPaid
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### ─── VERIFY DOCUMENT FLOW ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### Final state of all documents
GET {{base}}/Inquiries('INQ000001')
GET {{base}}/Quotations('QT000001')
GET {{base}}/SalesOrders('SO000001')
GET {{base}}/Deliveries?$filter=salesOrder_ID eq 'SO000001'
GET {{base}}/Invoices

### Check stock was reduced after GI
GET {{base}}/Products
